(firstQuint)Study of Glaucoma Treatment With Food Additives.

 Glaucomatous neuropathy is a condition that worsens with time causing atrophy of the optic nerve and narrowing of the visual field which may culminate in blindness.

 The treatment tested in the trial employs certain food additives intended to reverse this pathology.

.

